மச்சி - Same Problem! Key Issue இன்னும் இருக்கு! 🎯
காரணம்:
AWS-ல இன்னும் பழைய my-key-pair இருக்கு - devops-key import ஆகலை!
Quick Fix - இதை மட்டும் பண்ணு!
Step 1: AWS Console - Key Delete & Import
1. AWS → EC2 → Key Pairs
2. my-key-pair → Delete பண்ணு
3. Actions → Import key pair
   Name: my-key-pair
   Paste: (கீழே இருக்க key-ஐ paste பண்ணு)
உன் Public Key (இதை copy பண்ணி paste பண்ணு):
ssh-rsa 
Step 2: Destroy & Apply
cd ~/my-infra/terraform
terraform destroy -target=aws_instance.jenkins -target=aws_instance.devops_tools -auto-approve

terraform apply -target=aws_security_group.app_sg -target=aws_instance.jenkins -target=aws_instance.devops_tools -auto-approve
Step 3: Inventory Update & Ping
cd ../ansible
nano inventory.ini
# புது IPs போடு

ansible all -m ping
மச்சி - முதல்ல AWS Console-ல Key delete & import பண்ணு! அதுதான் root cause! 🔥
echo "ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAICLSGe5tEZ3tEe07MI3vYI05sgS7EXbNi5D8EH5yQlJk kiaq-lap-73@kiaq-lap-73" >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys


use பண்ணு:
# Step 1: புது RSA key create பண்ணு
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/ansible-key -N ""

# Step 2: Public key பாரு
cat ~/.ssh/ansible-key.pub
AWS Console-ல:
EC2 → Key Pairs → Create key pair
Name: ansible-key
→ அல்லது Import பண்ணு (ansible-key.pub content paste பண்ணு)
# Step 3: variables.tf மாத்து
cd ~/my-infra/terraform
nano variables.tf
# key_name = "ansible-key" போடு

# Step 4: Instances recreate
terraform destroy -target=aws_instance.jenkins -target=aws_instance.devops_tools -auto-approve
terraform apply -target=aws_security_group.app_sg -target=aws_instance.jenkins -target=aws_instance.devops_tools -auto-approve

# Step 5: inventory update
cd ../ansible
cat > inventory.ini << 'EOF'
[jenkins_server]
jenkins ansible_host=NEW_IP ansible_user=ec2-user ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/.ssh/ansible-key

[devops_tools_server]
devops ansible_host=NEW_IP ansible_user=ec2-user ansible_ssh_private_key_file=~/.ssh/ansible-key
EOF

ansible all -m ping
மச்சி இதுதான் cleanest solution - ssh-keygen command run பண்ணு! 🎯

cat > roles/sonarqube/tasks/main.yml << 'EOF'
---
- name: Install Java 21 for SonarQube
  shell: |
    if ! java -version 2>&1 | grep -q "21"; then
      wget https://corretto.aws/downloads/latest/amazon-corretto-21-x64-linux-jdk.rpm -O /tmp/java21.rpm
      yum install -y /tmp/java21.rpm
    fi

- name: Set vm.max_map_count
  sysctl:
    name: vm.max_map_count
    value: "524288"
    state: present
    reload: yes

- name: Set fs.file-max
  sysctl:
    name: fs.file-max
    value: "131072"
    state: present
    reload: yes

- name: Install unzip
  yum:
    name: unzip
    state: present

- name: Download SonarQube
  get_url:
    url: https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonarqube/sonarqube-10.4.1.88267.zip
    dest: /opt/sonarqube.zip
    timeout: 120

- name: Extract SonarQube
  unarchive:
    src: /opt/sonarqube.zip
    dest: /opt/
    remote_src: yes

- name: Create SonarQube User
  user:
    name: sonarqube
    system: yes

- name: Set Permissions
  file:
    path: /opt/sonarqube-10.4.1.88267
    owner: sonarqube
    group: sonarqube
    recurse: yes

- name: Create Systemd Service
  copy:
    dest: /etc/systemd/system/sonarqube.service
    content: |
      [Unit]
      Description=SonarQube
      After=network.target
      [Service]
      Type=forking
      User=sonarqube
      ExecStart=/opt/sonarqube-10.4.1.88267/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh start
      ExecStop=/opt/sonarqube-10.4.1.88267/bin/linux-x86-64/sonar.sh stop
      Restart=always
      LimitNOFILE=65536
      LimitNPROC=4096
      [Install]
      WantedBy=multi-user.target

- name: Start SonarQube
  systemd:
    name: sonarqube
    state: started
    enabled: yes
    daemon_reload: yes
EOF
ansible devops_tools_server -i inventory.ini -m shell -a "sudo systemctl status sonarqube" -b
